          "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
          "date": "2013-11-15 21:40:19.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-12-02 12:06:50.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-4194 ldlm: Make OBD_[ALLOC|FREE]_LARGE use consistent",
        "message": "LU-4194 ldlm: Make OBD_[ALLOC|FREE]_LARGE use consistent\n\nstruct ldlm_lock's l_lvb_data field is freed in ldlm_lock_put()\nusing OBD_FREE.  However, some other code paths can attach\na buffer to l_lvb_data that was allocated using OBD_ALLOC_LARGE.\nThis can lead to a kfree() of a vmalloc()ed buffer, which can\ntrigger a kernel Oops.\n\nChange-Id: Ic75a67530862eeb4d065c14bbbac80939bff5731\nSigned-off-by: Christopher J. Morrone <morrone2@llnl.gov>\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/8298\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Faccini Bruno <bruno.faccini@intel.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
